[C:personaggi"Characters"]

  [C:elena"Elena Ferro"]
  
  Protagonist, 38 years old, antique book restorer. Has worked at the City Library for ten years. Precise, methodical, accustomed to handling fragile things with care. After her father's death two years ago, she withdrew into herself.
  
    [C:elena-aspetto"Physical appearance"]
    
    Brown hair pulled back, reading glasses always hanging from her neck, well-kept hands but marked by solvents.
    
    [C:elena-voce"Way of speaking"]
    
    Short, precise sentences. Rarely raises her voice. When nervous, she takes her glasses off and puts them back on.

  [C:giorgio"Giorgio Mante"]
  
  72 years old, former antiquarian bookseller, now retired. Knew Elena's father. Carries a secret about a book that disappeared thirty years ago.

  [C:padre"Riccardo Ferro"]
  
  Elena's father, who died two years before the story begins. He was a librarian. Giorgio reveals that he had found something important shortly before dying.

[C:luoghi"Places"]

  [C:biblioteca"City Library"]
  
  An 18th-century palace in the historic center. The restoration laboratory is in the basement: artificial light, smell of glue and old paper, metal shelves.

  [C:libreria"The Catalogue Bookshop"]
  
  Giorgio's former shop, now closed. Dusty window, faded sign. Giorgio takes Elena there to show her something.

  [C:casa"Elena's Home"]
  
  An orderly apartment, almost bare. Boxes of her father's belongings still unopened in one room.

